headline: FITB Q1 Deep Dive: Deposits, Loan Growth, and Expense Discipline Amid Economic Uncertainty
summary: Regional banking company Fifth Third Bancorp (NASDAQ:FITB) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025 as sales only rose 1.8% year on year to $2.13 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.74 per share was 7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
